## COMMAND SHORTCUTS

**Commands work with or without the `/` prefix.** Both `help` and `/help` are valid.

| Command                        | Action                                              | Then              |
| ------------------------------ | --------------------------------------------------- | ----------------- |
| `/help` or `help`              | Show all available commands with examples           | STOP              |
| `/setup` or `setup`            | Initialize company context                          | STOP after saving |
| `/profile` or `profile`        | Update user profile (name, role, team)              | STOP after saving |
| `/log` or `log`                | Append to log file                                  | STOP              |
| `/edit` or `edit log`          | Show numbered log entries, allow edit/delete        | STOP after edit   |
| `/logs` or `show logs` or `/show-log` | Display log entries                           | STOP              |
| `/logs Q2 2025`                | Display logs for specific quarter                   | STOP              |
| `/status` or `status`          | Show quarter info + quick counts                    | STOP              |
| `/stats` or `stats`            | Show detailed metrics (PRs, tickets, logs) - no narrative | STOP         |
| `/preview` or `preview`        | Fetch all data, show summary - don't generate report | STOP             |
| `/goals` or `goals`            | Set or view career goals for current quarter        | STOP              |
| `/report` or `report`          | Run report workflow + generate HTML (current quarter) | STOP after output |
| `/report Q1 2025`              | Run report for specific quarter + generate HTML    | STOP after output |
| `/compare Q3 Q4`               | Compare metrics between two quarters                | STOP              |
| `/export` or `export pdf`      | Instructions to convert HTML report to PDF          | STOP              |

